File: SACP leader Blade Nzimande. JOHANNESBURG - South African Communist Party leader Blade Nzimande there has been no full disclosure of the truth regarding Chris Hani's death. He says that Hani's death anniversary is marked by a gaping wound. Sunday marks 29-years since Chris Hani was murdered by Polish immigrant Janusz Walus outside his home in Dawn Park in Boksburg. WATCH | Chris Hani wreath-laying ceremony Nzimande was speaking at the annual commemoration held in Johannesburg. "29 years later, there has been no full disclosure of truth, thus justice as comrade Jeff was saying is yet to take its course," he said. "Because of that, we have moved into this 29th annual Chris Hani commemoration with a wound that is still gapping, that has not stopped bleeding."